{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10600", "repo": "rails", "body": "If I would have to run: `load 'output_safety.rb'` 1000 times in my app I would agree with you.\r\nBut more likely I will run: `ActiveSupport::SafeBuffer#capitalize` more often. \r\nSo definition time makes zero sense to me. Even if you win that much it will be lost during 10 minutes a running app.\r\n\r\nBut I agree with memory usage concerns of `class_eval`, but I still prefer performance over memory consumption.\r\nAs I said before: Only for tiny methods like this `class_eval` is better.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dd47bd3543c151008abf"}, "issue_id": 10600, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/17923507", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10600#issuecomment-17923507", "updated_at": "2013-05-15T07:17:34Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan", "login": "bogdan", "gravatar_id": "91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2", "html_url": "https://github.com/bogdan", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F926d19e70f74c20f796d376aafa3c6e2.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 122436, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-05-15T07:17:34Z", "id": 17923507, "owner": "rails"}
